# opencode tab aliases for the /tabs-name command.
#
# /tabs-name names each iTerm2 tab after its project folder(s). By default it
# uses the folder basename; add lines here to map a project to a short label
# so the command reproduces your own short names instead of raw basenames.
#
# Format (one per line):   <key>=<label>
#   <key>    a full directory path (most specific) OR a folder basename
#   <label>  the short name to show in the tab
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored. A full-path key wins over
# a basename key when both match.
#
# Examples:
#   opencode-idle-dim=DIMM
#   researchs=RSRCH
#   /Users/you/Desktop/playground/BOMBO/FINANCES=FINANCES
